, Morgane still manages to seem out of the way, doubly so in the shady backyard. There, enjoy a perfect lamb burger, pink in the middle and slabbed with goat cheese that's coarse-textured and tart. You might hallucinate you're standing on a hillside and talking to a shepherd."},"4":{"Raw":"20c1\/8141511.t.jpg","Photo":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141511.87.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141511.132.jpg","Credit":"&nbsp;","Caption":"Lamb Burger at Morgane"},"5":{"Raw":"da26\/8141510.t.jpg","Photo":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141510.87.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141510.132.jpg","Credit":"&nbsp;","Caption":"<b>7. <a href=\"http:\/\/blogs.villagevoice.com\/forkintheroad\/2012\/08\/10_best_ny_burg.php\" target=\"_blank\">Peruvian Burger at Morocho<\/a><\/b><br\/>This humble cart, usually parked on the sidewalk of Union Square West, spends about 15 minutes on every burger. It's got to saut the sweet plantain, cook the thick ground-beef patty, and fry the egg just enough so the yolk bursts over the patty and dribbles on the bun. What a mess! But a delicious mess."},"6":{"Raw":"6eff\/8141508.t.jpg","Photo":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141508.87.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141508.132.jpg","Credit":"&nbsp;","Caption":"<b>6. <a href=\"http:\/\/www.voiceplaces.com\/perry-street-new-york-2493301-l\/\" target=\"_blank\">Yellowfin Burger at Perry St<\/a><\/b><br\/>Sure this place's regular burger is great (shown yesterday in a teaser post), but what really blew me away was the tuna burger, a perfect merging of yellowtail tartare and the burger ethos. The outside of the patty arrives nicely seared, while the interior is pure squish. The patty is topped with bonito mayonnaise and shiso leaf, sending it sprawling. And this being a Vongerichten joint, the homemade potato chips are perfect, too."},"7":{"Raw":"16c2\/8141517.t.jpg","Photo":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141517.87.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141517.132.jpg","Credit":"&nbsp;","Caption":"<b>5. <a href=\"http:\/\/www.voiceplaces.com\/masak-new-york-4408168-l\/\" target=\"_blank\">Rendang Burger at Masak<\/a><\/b><br\/>Introduced by the Dutch centuries ago, beef is the signature meat of Sumatra and rendang its most perfect usage. In this case, Singaporean-inspired Masak turns it into a delicious burger, accompanied by \"ketjap\" (the original Southeast Asian ketchup) and turmeric-coated pickled vegetables. If you're looking for a burger with all sorts of exotic flavors, this is a powerful contender."},"8":{"Raw":"b068\/8141518.t.jpg","Photo":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141518.87.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141518.132.jpg","Credit":"&nbsp;","Caption":"Masak"},"9":{"Raw":"c028\/8141506.t.jpg","Photo":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141506.87.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141506.132.jpg","Credit":"&nbsp;","Caption":"<b>4. <a href=\"http:\/\/www.voiceplaces.com\/bowery-diner-new-york-4408194-l\/\" target=\"_blank\">Bowery Special at Bowery Diner<\/a><\/b><br\/>The flagship burger at this agreeable updated French diner throws a stout plank of pastrami atop the ground-beef patty, then garnishes the pair with melted Swiss and grainy mustard, in a perfect conjoinment of two iconic New York foods."},"10":{"Raw":"0b4e\/8141505.t.jpg","Photo":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141505.87.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141505.132.jpg","Credit":"&nbsp;","Caption":"<b>3. <a href=\"http:\/\/www.voiceplaces.com\/mile-end-new-york-12856917-l\/\" target=\"_blank\">Breakfast Burger at Mile End Sandwich<\/a><\/b><br\/> Handily extending the temporal territory during which a burger can be enjoyed into the early morning, the wonderful breakfast burger features a savory veal sausage patty, runny fried egg, Quebecois muffin, and runaway slatherings of maple syrup and apple butter, touching base at \"Healthy\" and \"Wholesome\" while also being as artery-clogging as breakfast can be."},"11":{"Raw":"07a1\/8141507.t.jpg","Photo":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141507.87.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141507.132.jpg","Credit":"&nbsp;","Caption":"<b>2. <a href=\"http:\/\/www.voiceplaces.com\/peels-new-york-2460448-l\/\" target=\"_blank\">Cheeseburger at Peels<\/a><\/b><br\/>Grass-fed beef cooked just right, cave-aged cheddar for snap, and an assortment of hipster pickles right inside the bun to send the thing off on crazy jags of flavor. And the fries are A1, too. Tear into this one and make a mess."},"12":{"Raw":"41ba\/8141514.t.jpg","Photo":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141514.87.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141514.132.jpg","Credit":"&nbsp;","Caption":"<b>1. <a href=\"http:\/\/www.voiceplaces.com\/marseille-new-york-2467460-l\/\" target=\"_blank\">Marseille Burger at Marseille<\/a><\/b><br\/> Channeling the flavors of Provence, the thick, juicy burger comes with greenery and a slice of tomato of unsurpassed ripeness, the formidable patty -- always done rare -- capped with Gruyere, caramelized onions, and on top of it all, like snow on an alp, a thick mantle of homemade, way-garlicky aioli. Game, set, match."},"13":{"Raw":"aaf1\/8141513.t.jpg","Photo":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141513.87.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141513.132.jpg","Credit":"&nbsp;","Caption":"Marseille"},"14":{"Raw":"0066\/8141515.t.jpg","Photo":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141515.87.jpg","Thumb":"http:\/\/media.villagevoice.com\/8141515.132.jpg","Credit":"&nbsp;","Caption":"Inside the burger at Marseille."}},
